title: Chapter 16: Retrace Our Hooves
description: Susie makes contact in another realm.

title: Chapter 4: Pepper's Funeral
description: With help from Pepper, Susie is able to lay a special dream of hers to rest.

title: Chapter 9: Storybook Susie
description: Susie details her travels around the world.

title: Chapter 10: The Last Witch
description: Hedgehog worries that she may be too little to make big witch decisions.

title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 2: Tiny Outburst Society
description: After discovering that young Mortimer doesn't have any friends, Oscar helps him start a new club on campus. But the monsters are forced to hide their newfound friendship from the school - and Stuart.

title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 3: Witches' Brew
description: Mortimer and the monsters must figure out how to send Oscar back to his own time, but the only person that can help is the foe of monsters everywhere: a witch. Will they all be able to work together to get Oscar back to Hedgehog?

title: Chapter 18: Swellington Boots
description: When a summer storm brews, the crew cozies up in the library.

title: Chapter 19: Weather Your Weather
description: Susie mulls over her past.

title: Chapter 15: Croissant Moon
description: The magical creatures work together to send Mildred on a mission so they can have a special bedtime.

title: Chapter 17: Meeting of Mounds
description: The Coven challenges The Cuties to an impromptu softball game.

title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 1: Unaccompanied Oscar
description: When Oscar isn't invited to Alexa's birthday party, Mortimer tries to make him feel better by telling him about a similar time in his life. Ever the glowworm, Oscar sneaks back in time to help a young Mortimer overcome the sad experience.

title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 3: There's A Racket In My Hope Chest
description: The witches search for Betsy - who doesn't want to be found. Can she learn to love being a witch as much as she loves being a ghost?

title: The Babies Chapter 2: Teacup Giant
description: Susie sends Alexa to the Fjords to train as a giant, but her small size causes her to lag behind. Will Alexa be able to fake it until she makes it - or are these boots too enormous to fill?

title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 2: Hot Corn Girls
description: On her 15th birthday, Susie must prepare for her Gibbous Rite Ceremony. Will Mildred be able to keep her chaotic magic in check for just one day so Susie can become the full witch woman of her dreams?

title: Chapter 1: The Legs
description: Susie must rely on Oscar and Hedgehog in unimaginable ways after a magic trick gone wrong.

title: Chapter 13: Jar Guard
description: Mildred's Friend tells a cautionary tale.

title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 1: Heathers
description: Susie's new little sister has a gift for magic, but it's causing problems for the community. Will Susie learn to accept that Mildred is more powerful, and will the townsfolk be able to accept the most powerful witch in the world?

title: Chapter 20: It Takes Time
description: The island welcomes a new era.

title: The Babies Chapter 1: Breakfast Errands
description: Frustrated that he doesn't know his magical identity, Oliver convinces Susie to tell him by means of nonviolent protest. Not wanting anyone in her house, Susie takes Oliver on a series of errands to help him figure it out.

title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 3: Nightcap
description: Barb and the elves band together to protect the source of all magic from a pair of fiendish intruders. But will Barb be able to outsmart two rascals as old as the world itself?

title: Chapter 3: See Bees? Gee! Bees!
description: Oscar heads to the Sasquatch Monastery in search of enlightenment.

title: Chapter 6: Miracle Rabbit
description: Oscar and Ramona run an errand on the moon.

title: Chapter 12: Night's Pockets
description: Pajamas and Jimjams try to find Time.

title: Chapter 14: Bear With Me
description: A surprise visitor arrives on Summer Camp Island.

title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 2: Hot Milk and Careless Whispers
description: Barb tries to soothe the spotted bears with a dreamy invention, but soon finds herself outnumbered. Will Barb be able to even the playing field - or will she become the bears' next snack?

title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 1: A Barb is Born
description: On the third day of the world, Barb tries to save the ferns from being eaten by the spotted bears. But the bears are only getting hungrier and hungrier - will Barb be able to stop the ferns from going extinct?

title: Chapter 7: The Three Grrs
description: Oscar helps the aliens with a special jester ritual that happens once every fifty years.

title: The Babies Chapter 3: Lem Is Nothing
description: After landing in trouble with Susie, Lem runs away to Frozen Time to hide at Ramona's but is soon sniffed out by the fearsome Jabberwock. Later, Lem must decide whose wrath is worse: that of the Jabberwock, or a very grumpy Suze.

title: Chapter 11: The Metaphysical Reserve
description: Susie steps through a portal into another realm.

title: Chapter 5: The Hits
description: Barb and the Alien King take an eventful walk around the island.

title: Chapter 8: Go Get Our Girls
description: Hedgehog and Oscar search for the missing coven members.

title: Chapter 2: If I Only Had a Wand
description: Hedgehog reckons with her mother's disapproval of magic.

title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 1: Burps 'n Sighs
description: On the eve of Ramona's exile to Frozen Time, Susie tries to get rid of the sad memory of their relationship, but soon finds herself haunted by the past.

title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 2: Boo Jeans
description: It's Betsy's first night on Summer Camp Island, and she's looking forward to a cozy evening in with a nice cup of tea. But when Alice convinces her to participate in an initiation ritual, Betsy gets lost in the woods.

title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 3: Mildred's Friend
description: Locked in a standoff with Susie over who will say sorry first, Mildred runs away to the woods and befriends a ghost. Will one of the McAllister sisters give in and apologize before the townsfolk run Mildred out of town?
